# Vonos — Environment Variables (local development)

Copy to `.env` at repo root and/or per-app as needed.

For staging/beta and production, see:
  docs/ENVIRONMENTS.md
  .env.staging.example
  .env.production.example

```bash
# Web (apps/web) — copy to apps/web/.env.local
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
# No trailing slash — e.g. https://vonos-backend-production.up.railway.app
# Set to `true` only to bypass login during UI-only work
NEXT_PUBLIC_SKIP_AUTH=false

# API (apps/api)
# Raise pool size on Neon if overview/report queries time out (P2024):
# ...@host/db?connection_limit=10&pool_timeout=30
# Or set PRISMA_CONNECTION_LIMIT / PRISMA_POOL_TIMEOUT (applied when URL omits them).
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://vonos:vonos@localhost:5432/vonos
PRISMA_CONNECTION_LIMIT=10
PRISMA_POOL_TIMEOUT=30
JWT_SECRET=change-me-in-production
JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRES=2h
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRES=7d
WEB_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
# Comma-separated allowed frontend origins for CORS (also merges with defaults).
# Example: WEB_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000,https://app.vonosautos.com,https://app.vonosautosmarket.com
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3001
# Set true to log every Prisma SQL + duration (local/staging audit only)
PRISMA_LOG_QUERIES=false
# Upstash Redis — REQUIRED for staging/prod. Without these, report/dashboard
# caches use in-memory fallback and reset on every deploy / multi-instance miss.
# Create a free DB at https://console.upstash.com → copy REST URL + token.
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
```

Start Postgres locally:

```bash
docker compose up -d
```
